data.description: A little piece of heaven is waiting for you just one mile outside of Dinwiddie County on the picturesque Baskerville Mill Road in Brunswick County.  You will be captivated with amazing views of this sweet homestead on 9.85 acres sitting perfectly amongst the trees hugging the edges of the private pond nestled in the back. This home is timeless, the original architecture untouched, boasting beautifully maintained hardwood floors, 2 fireplaces, serene water views & meticulously crafted built-ins are the perfect sentimental touch to keep this mid-century farmhouse in its classic charm while providing all the creature comforts of the 21st century. The kitchen is adorned with stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, walk-in pantry, a modern farmhouse sink, updated ceiling fans throughout the home, newer HVAC and windows are just a bonus. Complete w/ full unfinished basement and a walk-up attic that could be easily turned into additional living space, or you can use it for easy access storage. 30 min commute to Colonial Heights, Blackstone, Fort Pickett, Lawrenceville, South Hill, and only 45 minutes to Fort Lee and 1 hour from Richmond. (10 min./7 miles from I85 in McKenney)
